					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The accurate way is to take the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_Fourier_transform" class="postlink">discrete Fourier transform</a> of the 12-point signal and discard all but the DC and the first AC coefficient. The DC gives you Y, and the real and imaginary parts of AC give you U and V. YUV is the same thing as YIQ modulo tint. Because you only need three coefficients (real DC, real AC[1], imaginary AC[1]), it'll probably take only 7 multiplies and 29 adds.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

