				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Saturation adjustment ("color" knob) multiplies each U and V by a scale factor. For hue adjustment ("tint" knob), shift the basis functions (sin() and cos() in this case). Given hue in radians, you can do this shift when setting up sintable[]:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">void initSintable&#40;float hue&#41; &#123;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; int i;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; for&#40;i = 0; i &lt; 15; i++&#41;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; sintable&#91;i&#93; = sin&#40;i * M_PI / 6 + hue&#41;;<br />&#125;<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
